			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">International Phonetic Alphabet</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><script>function mfTempOpenSection(id){var block=document.getElementById("mf-section-"+id);block.className+=" open-block";block.previousSibling.className+=" open-block";}</script><div role="note" class="hatnote">"IPA" redirects here. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/IPA_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="IPA (disambiguation)">IPA (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote">Not to be confused with <a href="/wiki/NATO_phonetic_alphabet" title="NATO phonetic alphabet">NATO phonetic alphabet</a> or <a href="/wiki/Americanist_phonetic_notation" title="Americanist phonetic notation">Americanist phonetic notation</a>.</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote"><span class="plainlinks selfreference noprint">For usage of IPA in Wikipedia, see <a href="/wiki/Help:IPA" title="Help:IPA">Help:IPA</a>, <a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Introduction" title="Help:IPA/Introduction">Help:IPA/Introduction</a> or <a href="/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English" title="Help:IPA for English">Help:IPA for English</a></span></div>
